TITLE: Using bpf_printk macro in eBPF program
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use the bpf_printk macro in an eBPF program. It shows two cases: one using bpf_trace_printk (with 3 or fewer arguments) and another using bpf_trace_vprintk (with more than 3 arguments).
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/ebpf-library/libbpf/ebpf/bpf_printk.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
SEC("tc")
int example_prog(struct __sk_buff *ctx)
{
    // Will use bpf_trace_printk
    bpf_printk(
        "Got a packet from interface %d, src: %pi4, dst: %pi4\n", 
        ctx->ingress_ifindex, 
        ctx->remote_ip4, 
        ctx->local_ip4,
    );

    // Will use bpf_trace_vprintk
    bpf_printk(
        "Got a packet from interface %d, src: %pi4, dst: %pi4, src port: %d, dst port: %d\n", 
        ctx->ingress_ifindex, 
        ctx->remote_ip4, 
        ctx->local_ip4,
        ctx->remote_port,
        ctx->local_port,
    );

    return TC_ACT_OK;
}
```

