TITLE: SKB Dynamic Pointer String Comparison in eBPF
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to use dynamic pointers to access SKB data and perform string comparison operations. It shows the usage of bpf_dynptr_from_skb and bpf_dynptr_slice functions, with error handling for NULL cases.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/linux/concepts/dynptrs.md#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
SEC("?cgroup_skb/egress")
int test_dynptr_skb_strcmp(struct __sk_buff *skb)
{
	struct bpf_dynptr ptr;
	char *data;

	if (bpf_dynptr_from_skb(skb, 0, &ptr)) {
		err = 1;
		return 1;
	}

	/* This may return NULL. SKB may require a buffer */
	data = bpf_dynptr_slice(&ptr, 0, NULL, 10);
	if (data) {
		bpf_strncmp(data, 10, "foo");
		return 1;
	}

	return 1;
}
```

