TITLE: Using Atomic Operations in eBPF to Count System Calls
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use atomic operations to safely increment a counter in a shared variable. The __sync_fetch_and_add atomic function is used to count the number of times the sys_enter tracepoint is called.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/linux/concepts/concurrency.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
int counter = 0;

SEC("tp_btf/sys_enter")
int sys_enter_count(void *ctx) {
	__sync_fetch_and_add(&counter, 1);
	return 0;
}
```

