TITLE: Implementing a Memory Protection Security Audit with LSM eBPF Program
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates an LSM eBPF program that attaches to the file_mprotect hook to audit and potentially block memory protection changes. It specifically checks if the memory area is in the heap region and returns an error (-EPERM) to block the operation if true.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/linux/program-type/BPF_PROG_TYPE_LSM.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
// Copyright (C) 2020 Google LLC.
SEC("lsm/file_mprotect")
int BPF_PROG(mprotect_audit, struct vm_area_struct *vma,
            unsigned long reqprot, unsigned long prot, int ret)
{
    /* ret is the return value from the previous BPF program
        * or 0 if it's the first hook.
        */
    if (ret != 0)
        return ret;

    int is_heap;

    is_heap = (vma->vm_start >= vma->vm_mm->start_brk &&
            vma->vm_end <= vma->vm_mm->brk);

    /* Return an -EPERM or write information to the perf events buffer
        * for auditing
        */
    if (is_heap)
        return -EPERM;
}
