TITLE: Defining the perf_event_mmap_page Structure in C
DESCRIPTION: This C code defines the `struct perf_event_mmap_page`, which represents the metadata header found on the first page of the memory region mapped by `mmap` for a perf event ring buffer. This structure contains crucial fields like `data_head` (kernel writes) and `data_tail` (userspace updates after reading) to manage the ring buffer, along with offset and size information (`data_offset`, `data_size`) and various capability flags and timing details.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/linux/map-type/BPF_MAP_TYPE_PERF_EVENT_ARRAY.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
