TITLE: Defining the BPF_KSYSCALL Macro in C
DESCRIPTION: This C macro definition (`BPF_KSYSCALL`) simplifies writing eBPF kprobe programs that attach to syscalls. It automatically handles variations in syscall calling conventions across different CPU architectures, particularly the presence of syscall wrappers (`CONFIG_ARCH_HAS_SYSCALL_WRAPPER`). The macro generates the necessary function signature and boilerplate code to extract syscall arguments correctly, making them directly available to the BPF program logic. It depends on BPF CO-RE and virtual `__kconfig` externs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/ebpf-library/libbpf/ebpf/BPF_KSYSCALL.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
#define BPF_KSYSCALL(name, args...)\
name(struct pt_regs *ctx);\
extern _Bool LINUX_HAS_SYSCALL_WRAPPER __kconfig;\
static __always_inline typeof(name(0))\
____##name(struct pt_regs *ctx, ##args);\
typeof(name(0)) name(struct pt_regs *ctx)\
{\
\tstruct pt_regs *regs = LINUX_HAS_SYSCALL_WRAPPER\
\t\t\t       ? (struct pt_regs *)PT_REGS_PARM1(ctx)\
\t\t\t       : ctx;\
\t_Pragma("GCC diagnostic push")\
\t_Pragma("GCC diagnostic ignored \"-Wint-conversion\"")\
\tif (LINUX_HAS_SYSCALL_WRAPPER)\
\t\treturn ____##name(___bpf_syswrap_args(args));\
\telse\
\t\treturn ____##name(___bpf_syscall_args(args));\
\t_Pragma("GCC diagnostic pop")\
}\
static __always_inline typeof(name(0))\
____##name(struct pt_regs *ctx, ##args)
```

