TITLE: Defining the MEMBER_VPTR Macro for eBPF
DESCRIPTION: The macro definition for MEMBER_VPTR which creates a verifier-friendly pointer to a struct or array member. It calculates the byte offset, checks against size bounds, and returns a NULL pointer if out-of-bounds to help satisfy the eBPF verifier.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/ebpf-library/scx/MEMBER_VPTR.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
#define MEMBER_VPTR(base, member) (typeof((base) member) *)             \
({                                                                      \
    u64 __base = (u64)&(base);                                          \
    u64 __addr = (u64)&((base) member) - __base;                        \
    _Static_assert(sizeof(base) >= sizeof((base) member),               \
               "@base is smaller than @member, is @base a pointer?");   \
    asm volatile (                                                      \
        "if %0 <= %[max] goto +2\n"                                     \
        "%0 = 0\n"                                                      \
        "goto +1\n"                                                     \
        "%0 += %1\n"                                                    \
        : "+r"(__addr)                                                  \
        : "r"(__base),                                                  \
          [max]"i"(sizeof(base) - sizeof((base) member)));              \
    __addr;                                                             \
})
```

