DESCRIPTION: This code snippet implements macros for converting values between network and host byte orders in C for eBPF programs, supporting both compile-time constants and runtime values. It uses system endianness checks and compiler builtins (such as __builtin_bswap16) when appropriate, ensuring efficient code generation. Dependencies include a C environment targeting eBPF, likely using libbpf; key parameters include the 16-bit number 'x'; outputs are converted values suitable for safe network/host interaction, and the code is limited to platforms whose compilers define __BYTE_ORDER__ macros.
