TITLE: Defining an eBPF Program for Socket Redirection in C
DESCRIPTION: This C code defines an eBPF program attached to the `sk_skb/stream_verdict` hook. It inspects the local port (`skb->local_port`). If the port is 10000, it uses the `bpf_sk_redirect_map` helper to redirect the socket via the `sock_map_rx` map at index 0. Otherwise, it allows the packet to pass through normally (`SK_PASS`). This program requires a userspace loader to create and manage the `sock_map_rx`.
