TITLE: Defining ARRAY_ELEM_PTR Macro for Verified Array Element Access in C
DESCRIPTION: This macro creates a verified pointer to an array element, particularly useful for arrays that will be resized before BPF program loading. It safely handles bounds checking to prevent verifier rejection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/ebpf-library/scx/ARRAY_ELEM_PTR.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
#define ARRAY_ELEM_PTR(arr, i, n) (typeof(arr[i]) *)    \
({                                                      \
    u64 __base = (u64)arr;                              \
    u64 __addr = (u64)&(arr[i]) - __base;               \
    asm volatile (                                      \
        "if %0 <= %[max] goto +2\n"                     \
        "%0 = 0\n"                                      \
        "goto +1\n"                                     \
        "%0 += %1\n"                                    \
        : "+r"(__addr)                                  \
        : "r"(__base),                                  \
          [max]"r"(sizeof(arr[0]) * ((n) - 1)));        \
    __addr;                                             \
})
```

