TITLE: Defining the 'container_of' Macro in C
DESCRIPTION: Provides the C preprocessor definition of the `container_of` macro. It calculates the address of the containing structure (`type`) by taking a pointer to a member (`ptr`), casting it to `void *`, and then subtracting the byte offset of that `member` within the `type` structure using the `offsetof` macro. The result is cast to a pointer of the containing structure's `type`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/ebpf-library/libbpf/ebpf/container_of.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
#define container_of(ptr, type, member)                 \
    ({                                                  \
        void *__mptr = (void *)(ptr);                   \
        ((type *)(__mptr - offsetof(type, member)));    \
    })
```

