TITLE: Definition of struct btf_type in C
DESCRIPTION: Structure definition for btf_type which represents BPF Type Format information. It includes name offset, info bits for storing metadata, and a union for size or type reference depending on the kind of type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/ebpf-library/libbpf/userspace/btf__type_by_id.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
struct btf_type {
    __u32 name_off;
    /* "info" bits arrangement
     * bits  0-15: vlen (e.g. # of struct's members)
     * bits 16-23: unused
     * bits 24-28: kind (e.g. int, ptr, array...etc)
     * bits 29-30: unused
     * bit     31: kind_flag, currently used by
     *             struct, union, fwd, enum and enum64.
     */
    __u32 info;
    /* "size" is used by INT, ENUM, STRUCT, UNION and ENUM64.
     * "size" tells the size of the type it is describing.
     *
     * "type" is used by PTR, TYPEDEF, VOLATILE, CONST, RESTRICT,
     * FUNC, FUNC_PROTO, DECL_TAG and TYPE_TAG.
     * "type" is a type_id referring to another type.
     */
    union {
            __u32 size;
            __u32 type;
    };
};
```

