TITLE: Registering UMEM with AF_XDP Socket in C
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to register the allocated UMEM with the AF_XDP socket using the setsockopt() system call.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/linux/concepts/af_xdp.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
struct xdp_umem_reg {
	__u64 addr; /* Start of packet data area */
	__u64 len; /* Length of packet data area */
	__u32 chunk_size;
	__u32 headroom;
	__u32 flags;
};

struct xdp_umem_reg umem_reg = {
    .addr = (__u64)(void *)umem,
    .len = umem_len,
    .chunk_size = chunk_size,
    .headroom = 0, // see Options, variations, and exceptions
    .flags = 0, // see Options, variations, and exceptions
};
if (!setsockopt(fd, SOL_XDP, XDP_UMEM_REG, &umem_reg, sizeof(umem_reg)))
    // handle error
```

