TITLE: Using Spin Locks in eBPF to Safely Update Map Values
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use bpf_spin_lock and bpf_spin_unlock helpers to safely increment a counter in a shared map value. The code initializes a map element if needed, then acquires the lock before modifying the value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/linux/concepts/concurrency.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
SEC("tp_btf/sys_enter")
int sys_enter_count(void *ctx) {
	int key = 0;
	struct concurrent_element init_value = {};
	struct concurrent_element *read_value;
	bpf_map_update_elem(&concurrent_map, &key, &init_value, BPF_NOEXIST);

	read_value = bpf_map_lookup_elem(&concurrent_map, &key);
	if(!read_value)
	{
		return 0;
	}

	bpf_spin_lock(&read_value->semaphore);
	read_value->count += 1;
	bpf_spin_unlock(&read_value->semaphore);
	return 0;
}
```

