TITLE: Implementing log2_u64 function in C for SCX eBPF
DESCRIPTION: This function computes the base 2 logarithm of a 64-bit value. It splits the input into high and low 32-bit parts, and uses the log2_u32 function for computation. The function handles both cases where the high 32 bits are set or not.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/ebpf-library/scx/log2_u64.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
static inline u32 log2_u64(u64 v)
{
        u32 hi = v >> 32;
        if (hi)
                return log2_u32(hi) + 32 + 1;
        else
                return log2_u32(v) + 1;
}
```

