TITLE: Using __bpf_unreachable in an eBPF switch statement
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates the use of __bpf_unreachable in a switch statement. It ensures that my_func is always called with one of the handled enum values, causing a compile-time error if an unhandled case is reached.
SOURCE: https://github.com/isovalent/ebpf-docs/blob/master/docs/ebpf-library/libbpf/ebpf/__bpf_unreachable.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
enum my_enum {
    MY_ENUM_A,
    MY_ENUM_B,
};

static void __always_inline my_func(enum my_enum e) {
    switch (e) {
    case MY_ENUM_A:
        // Do something
        break;
    case MY_ENUM_B:
        // Do something
        break;
    default:
        __bpf_unreachable();
    }
}
```

